Do you believe the war on drugs is effective? If so....how do you justify the government spending millions (possibly billions) of dollars, and the problem is much worse then before the war started? (and don't tell me the problem is getting better) If you think this war is a complete wash...how would YOU propose to fix things? <br>
<br>
My thoughts - <br>
Playboy readers, refer to the Playboy January 2001 issue, interview with Gary Johnson, governor of New Mexico. He proposes to legalize pot and heroin, but controlling it, in a way that I think would work. Pot is less dangerous than alcohol...safer then tobacco....and if legalized would make it safer for teens and other pot heads to get the drugs they would buy anyway, and the government would make a MINT off of the profits. Heroin is (so I hear, never done in myself) very dangerous...and leads to far too many deaths and the cost to Americans is HUGE...if legalized, the government would manufacture the stuff safely, the addicts would get their prescriptions from a doctor....maybe even go to a clinic.<br>
<br>
This SOLVES...completely SOLVES drug dealers...drug pushers....gets rid of the possibility of overdoses, bad batches of the product...removes the danger to our kids getting ahold of the stuff. Ok...great ...but it also saves MONEY and makes the police force more effective - the judicial system is no longer clogged up with drug cases, the police have more time to deal with REAL criminals....<br>
<br>
Do you agree or not? Don't flame me, just add your thoughts...and BTW...yes I used to smoke pot, but not for...hell 7 years..and thats all I've done (illegally anyway hehehe) <p><Br>
