<br>
Sure, pot isn't as harmful as cigs or alcohol, I have to agree with you.  But I don't think that's good grounds for legalizing it.  That's rationalizing one vice with another.  To be honest I think cigarettes should be outlawed too in order to protect people from themselves, but that would never go over because people are paranoid of government interference with their private lives and freedom of choice.  Obviously outlawing alcohol doesn't work, it's rooted in culture.  So while both those substances would be make society better off if they were outlawed, execution would never happen, so it doesn't pay to outlaw them.  I just don't think we should add another substance to that list.<br>
